messages.content: Python asyncio is a library for writing concurrent code using the async/await syntax. It provides an event loop that manages coroutines.
Can you explain event loops in more detail?
An event loop runs async tasks and callbacks, handles I/O events, and manages subprocesses. It is the core of every asyncio application.
